<br>
way back nag and vox were the uberest mobs, and were up all the time<br>
some high level guilds slowly formed up and started killing them<br>
at the time with the very small number of 50s they had to work together<br>
<br>
kunark came out, guilds were more powerful and after a while leveling and learning the zones, trakanon was killed, along with the other ubermobs<br>
the big guild were sharing them, but as lesser (i dont mean to be insulting or ironic but this, it's just a plain fact that they are not as powerful, doesnt mean they are not as worthy) were reaching up, they had less and less spawns for themselves<br>
<br>
right now the high level population is so big the common ubermobs are killed every spawn with a long waiting list<br>
<br>
is there a difference between fear and growth ? no not really, but the big raiders and the general mood of the server has changed<br>
cooperation is not needed anymore, and sharing becomes annoying when you have to share with too many people<br>
<br>
the guilds of this server are now closer of the guilds of the other servers, able to more or less just raid by themselves with some invites<br>
<br>
and they are jealous of other servers where they would get most spawns..<br>
<br>
nothing has really changed in the way verant designs the zones, ubermobs still have a set spawn time, they are left almost alone until the server learns how easy it is to kill them...<br>
<br>
you can bet in 2 months wuoshi and kelorek will be killed on a regular basis, laking nillon's reason bogus, but that wont change anything, the server as a whole is thinking differently, and it will slowly move from this odd position where the strong has to leave room for the weak, to a more normal position where uberguilds (ya ya not uber whatever) get most spawns and loot<br>
<br>
until then we can keep dreaming of a perfect world where everyone would be able to kill anything when they want to <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Gimp</span><br>  Posts: 636<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/26/01 12:47:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/BrianPic_copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hurting vs helping</span><hr size=1> PoG is a hot spot eh? dunno, i've walked in there 6 of the last 9 days and found noone there. The whole issue is being dreamed up by a couple of people cause they want to be able to exclude others and get phat lewts. The people who are limiting access to PoG aren't the ones who want fcfs people, cause even the uberest guilds on this server arent big enough to dominate every spawn like the other uberservers do, and probably never will be. The people who want to limit your access are the ones who want to create endless rotations and reservations lists on areas that were created by verant specifically to discourage those practices because of their huge size, number of mobs, and odd respawn times. <br>
<br>
You want to support more raiding on this server? You want people to get MORE chances to raid? keep Velious fcfs a while and see how often you get to hit the areas you want, versus how long you'd have had to wait if you were 17th on some ridiculous list. I'm serious about this, think about it. <br>
